comment._content:
Your picture shows an Otto pusher biplane competing in the Military Competition [Militärflug-Wettbewerb] held on 19, 20 and 21 October 1913 in Oberschleißheim airfield near München. This machine with competition number '7' was powered by a 100 hp Mercedes engine and flown by Lt. Martin Demmel and Lt. Cornelius Vogeley. 

Otto pusher biplane with competition number '7' of the Military competition held in October 1913 around München.
